<title type="html"><![CDATA[triangle channel problems: blargg are you there?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=874&amp;p=7791#p7791"><![CDATA[
If it is setting the triangle channel's period to an "impossibly" low number (less than about 7), and you're hearing spurious high frequencies, then odds are you're hearing aliasing. To make aliasing less apparent you need to oversample and filter the audio signal. For a first approximation, try sampling every 27 cycles and averaging each three samples.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Wed Dec 28, 2005 6:52 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
